cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it introduces a family of fast, flexible, and general-purpose kernel learning methods. It also compares the proposed methods with existing alternatives in terms of accuracy, speed, and memory consumption. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it deals with learning rich statistical representations of large datasets. The paper may also be relevant to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as kernel methods are commonly used in image processing and computer vision tasks. The Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper proposes mechanisms to learn the properties of groups of spectral frequencies in Fastfood basis function expansions. Finally, the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper compares the proposed methods with neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning tasks.
